[2] Russia: record high cases
Date: Sat 6 Nov 2021
Source: TASS [edited]
https://tass.com/society/1358187


Russia recorded 41 335 coronavirus cases in the past 24 hours, the highest daily number since the onset of the pandemic, the anti-coronavirus crisis center said on Saturday [6 Nov 2021]. The total number of cases has reached 8 755 930. According to data from the crisis center, Russia's coronavirus growth rate was 0.47%. The country's new daily coronavirus cases exceed 40 000 for the 4th day in a row.

In particular, 3138 cases were reported in St Petersburg in the past day, 1621 in the Samara region, 795 in the Voronezh and Nizhny Novgorod regions, and 776 in Crimea.

There are currently 975 123 active coronavirus cases in Russia. Russia's coronavirus recoveries rose by 29 201 to 7 535 172 in the past 24 hours. According to data from the crisis center, 86.06% of coronavirus patients have recovered in Russia. In particular, 3330 recoveries were confirmed in St. Petersburg in the past day, 986 in the Samara region, 701 in Crimea, 690 in the Krasnoyarsk region, and 669 in the Bashkortostan region.

Russia recorded 1188 coronavirus deaths in the past 24 hours, down from 1192 the day before. The total coronavirus death toll has climbed to 245 635. According to data from the crisis center, 2.81% of coronavirus patients have died in Russia. In particular, 86 coronavirus fatalities were reported in St Petersburg in the past day, 46 in the Krasnodar region and 40 in the Voronezh region. The Stavropol and Perm regions recorded 41 deaths each.

--
communicated by:
ProMED rapporteur Kunihiko Iizuka

[According to the Worldometer (https://www.worldometers.info/coronavirus/coronavirus-death-rate/), Infection Fatality Rate (IFR) = Deaths / Cases [that is: deaths + recovered cases]. Using today's worldwide data = 5 060 131 / 231 million = 2.2% (2.2% of people infected with SARS-CoV-2 have a fatal outcome, while 97.8% recover). The report above says that 2.8% of COVID patients in Russia have died, but the data above (245 635 deaths and 7 535 172 recoveries) -- which tally with today's Worldometer data -- suggest an IFR of 3.2%, a little higher than for the world overall. But the report also states that 86.1% of patients have recovered, leaving about 11% unaccounted for. These numbers are difficult to compare though, because many cases are not confirmed and not included in the calculation. See https://ourworldindata.org/mortality-risk-covid for a discussion of the different presentations of mortality rate. - Mod.LK]

