[In the past 24 hours, 11 countries including Russia (41 335), the USA (32 479), the UK (30 539), Germany (26 389), Turkey (27 474), Ukraine (25 063), Poland (15 204), the Netherlands (11 954), Brazil (11 866), Belgium (10 915), and India (10 879) all reported more than 10 000 newly confirmed cases. A global total of 6318 deaths were reported in the past 24 hours (late 3 Nov 2021 to late 4 Nov 2021). A total of 55 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours; 32 of the 53 countries are from the European region, 6 are from the Americas region, 4 are from the Eastern Mediterranean region, 4 are from the South East Asia region, 6 are from the Western Pacific region, and 1 from the African region.

Comparing the 7-day averages of daily confirmed cases from the past 7 days and those from 8-14 days ago, case counts have increased by 1.1%, while daily reported deaths have decreased by 2.9%. Similar comparative 7-day averages in the USA show a 0.99% decrease in daily reported cases and a 14.6% decrease in reported deaths.

Impression: The global daily reported over 400 000 newly confirmed infections in the past 24 hours with over 250.27 million cumulative reported cases and over 5.06 million reported deaths. - Mod.UBA]
